you came to discover her music?

00:16:09.130 --> 00:16:11.660
&gt;&gt; Anne Sofie von Otter:
Yeah, Eva Cassidy --

00:16:11.660 --> 00:16:16.440
I wonder if her friend didn't say
have you heard of Eva Cassidy?

00:16:16.440 --> 00:16:18.430
I think so.

00:16:18.430 --> 00:16:24.780
And then I was hunting around
for Simon and Garfunkel songs,

00:16:24.780 --> 00:16:27.240
and on Spotify, her name came up.

00:16:27.240 --> 00:16:28.540
And I recognized the name.

00:16:28.540 --> 00:16:32.680
And I listened and
then it's so beautiful,

00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:35.710
and I went out to buy a disc.

00:16:35.710 --> 00:16:40.200
But I, and most of the world,
didn't know who she was

00:16:40.200 --> 00:16:41.640
when she was still alive.

00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:46.580
Apparently she really wasn't
famous outside Washington.

00:16:46.580 --> 00:16:51.500
And then somebody did
put together some songs

00:16:51.500 --> 00:16:53.740
or made a program about her.

00:16:53.740 --> 00:16:58.830
And then she -- you know people
heard how beautifully she sang.

00:16:58.830 --> 00:17:02.490
But she didn't -- she had a --
you know she [inaudible] so much

00:17:02.490 --> 00:17:07.340
in a much tougher way, but she
really knew how to use her voice.

00:17:07.340 --> 00:17:10.790
It's very sad that
she died so early.

